Practical classes, new topic is introduced in a theoretical lecture. Technical drawing tools, paper formats, scales, standards of formatting, main terminology of practical geometry, isometry, types of perspective. Symbols. Scaling of a drawing. Adding explanatory texts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To develop the student's ability to read drawings and their skills in constructing spatial models on the basis of drawings. To provide an overview of the professional application of technical drawing.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successfully completing the course the student: has an overview of the main drawing tools; knows the standards used in technical drawing and formatting requirements; knows how to sketch ideas; knows how to scale a drawing; knows the principles of section and perspective design; knows the symbols used in technical drawing; knows how to create isometric drawings i.e. create a 3D view of the object.
